{"batch":"Architecture & Coupling","batch_index":1,"assessments":{"cross_module_architecture":82.0},"dimension_notes":{"cross_module_architecture":{"evidence":["Contract identity and semantics are authored in multiple places: canonical IDs in goseg/protocol/actionids/actionids.go, catalog specs in goseg/protocol/contracts/familycatalog/catalog.go, and behavior assertions in goseg/uploadsvc/actions_test.go and goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/contractspec_test.go.","goseg/protocol/contracts/family_specs_test.go builds family entries with duplicated literal Name/Description/Message values rather than consuming familycatalog declarations, which creates parallel sources for contract metadata.","goseg/protocol/contracts/conformance/fixtures_test.go imports groundseg/uploadsvc to validate parser/actions from within protocol contract conformance tests, creating reverse test-time coupling from protocol contracts to a service module."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"}},"findings":[{"dimension":"cross_module_architecture","identifier":"fragmented_action_contract_authority","summary":"Action-contract ownership is fragmented across protocol catalog, action ID constants, and upload service tests, creating boundary drift risk.","related_files":["goseg/protocol/actionids/actionids.go","goseg/protocol/contracts/familycatalog/catalog.go","goseg/protocol/contracts/family_specs_test.go","goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/contractspec_test.go"],"evidence":["`actionids.go` defines namespace/action/contract-id primitives while `familycatalog/catalog.go` separately defines action names/descriptions/owners for the same actions.","`family_specs_test.go` uses inline literals (e.g., \"upload open endpoint\", \"open upload endpoint contract\", \"upload open endpoint message\") instead of deriving from catalog specs, so metadata can diverge without a compile-time boundary.","`contractspec_test.go` validates count and membership alignment between uploadsvc and contractspec, but does not centralize the authority; consistency relies on cross-package tests rather than a single dependency direction."],"suggestion":"Create a single canonical contract declaration module (IDs + metadata + ownership) consumed by both protocol contracts and uploadsvc, and replace duplicated literals in tests with generated/derived expectations from that source to enforce one-way dependency and reduce drift.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"missing_single_contract_authority"},{"dimension":"cross_module_architecture","identifier":"protocol_tests_depend_on_service_impl","summary":"Protocol conformance tests depend directly on upload service APIs, introducing reverse layer coupling and larger blast radius for service changes.","related_files":["goseg/protocol/contracts/conformance/fixtures_test.go","goseg/uploadsvc/actions_test.go","goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/contractspec_test.go"],"evidence":["`fixtures_test.go` imports `groundseg/uploadsvc` and calls `SupportedUploadActions`, `UploadActionContractByAction`, and `ParseUploadAction` from a protocol contracts test package.","This makes protocol contract conformance test outcomes contingent on uploadsvc parser implementation details, not only contract declarations.","Adjacent uploadsvc tests already validate parser and contract map behavior, so protocol-layer tests are crossing boundaries to revalidate service behavior."],"suggestion":"Move uploadsvc parser conformance checks into uploadsvc-owned contract tests (or a dedicated integration layer) and keep protocol conformance tests limited to protocol declaration artifacts/interfaces. If cross-layer checks are needed, define a narrow adapter interface in protocol tests and satisfy it from integration tests.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"missing_single_contract_authority"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Contract metadata lacks a single authoritative boundary, so consistency is enforced by distributed tests instead of dependency structure.","Conformance responsibilities are split across protocol and upload service tests, causing layer ownership blur."],"likely_symptoms":["fragmented_action_contract_authority","protocol_tests_depend_on_service_impl"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}
